[size=5]Installation[/size]
[list]
[*] [b]Game Version:[/b] Works with version 1.0 of the game.
[*] [b]Install with Vortex:[/b] Use the [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/about/vortex/]Vortex Mod Manager[/url] to install the mod easily.
[*] [b]Optional Customization:[/b]
[list]
[*] For more in-game options, you can install the [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/7daystodie/mods/4017]Gears[/url] and [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/7daystodie/mods/2409/]Quartz[/url] mods.
[*] You can also customize the mod manually by editing the [b]ModSettings.xml[/b] file.
[/list][/list]


[size=5]Features[/size]
[list]
[*] The crosshair appears only when needed:
[list]
[*] It shows up when you're holding a tool, using your hands, or hovering over an interactable object.
[*] It automatically appears when an interaction prompt is available (like opening doors or interacting with cars), no matter what you have equipped.[/list]
[*] You can customize how the crosshair behaves in different situations:
[list]
[*] [b]Bows (no sights):[/b] Choose between turning the crosshair off or having it stay on.
[*] [b]Tools and hands:[/b] Choose to have the crosshair off, on only when needed, or always on.
[*] [b]Melee weapons:[/b] Choose to turn the crosshair off, have it appear dynamically, or keep it on all the time.
[*] [b]Ranged weapons:[/b] You can turn the crosshair off or keep it on.[/list]
[*] The mod uses the game's built-in system to detect how close you are to objects, ensuring the crosshair behaves accurately.
[*] It's also compatible with the [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/7daystodie/mods/5640]Dot Crosshair[/url] mod if you want a simpler crosshair option.
[*] [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/7daystodie/mods/5601?tab=videos#lg=2&slide=0]See the mod in action on the Videos tab[/url].
[/list]
